==English==

===Etymology===
From Latinized {{Gr.}} ''[[electrinus]]'' "made of amber", from [[Ancient Greek]]  '''[[ἤλεκτρον]]''' (''elektron'') "amber", from '''[[ἠλέκτωρ]]''' (''elektor'') "shiny, bright", from '''[[ἥλιος]]''' (''helios'') "sun". <small>(''See the [[Talk:electric|Talk page]])</small>

